CONDITIONS MODIFIED 02-25-2022:  The Court will allow the Defendant to return to his home.  The defendant is not to be located on the school grounds at all.  Defendant is still to comply with the GPS monitoring.   

PREVIOUS CONDITIONS: If DNA sample has not been taken from the defendant, the Court orders sample to be taken;  and it may be expunged under 165.77(4) Wis. Statutes.  Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing.  Defendant to have no contact with victim A (or their family)/witness A (or their family) listed in the Criminal Complaint/Victim Identification Key.  Defendant is not to share, reproduce or distribute any personal and/or identifying information about the crime victim(s), except to their attorney. Defendant not to leave the State of Wisconsin without prior authorization from the Court.  Defendant to surrender their passport to the Waukesha Criminal Traffic Office (Room C226) within 24 hours of release from custody.  Defendant to comply with GPS monitoring through Wisconsin Community Services.  Defendant is not to come within 3 miles of Victims A/Witness A, listed in the Victim Identification Key, or their residence, employment, school or anywhere they frequent.   Defendant to be released during regular business hours only and is to report directly to Wisconsin Community Services upon release.   Absolute sobriety, defendant is not to possess or consume any alcohol.  Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed.  Defendant not to possess any drug paraphernalia.   Defendant to have no unsupervised contact with any child under the age of 18. Defendant is prohibited from accessing any child exploitation material and any other sexually explicit material through the Internet or by any other means.  Defendant prohibited from contacting a minor over the internet or using a website to gather information about a minor. Defendant is prohibited from intentionally deleting any history from any computer or device that accesses the Internet. Defendant prohibited from using any application where the content automatically deletes upon the recipient opening the content.

Court to address defense motion to modify bail.  Attorney Nicholson presents arguments in support of the motion to modify.  State has no objection to the bail request but that the defendant not go to the school.  Court will grant the motion to modify bail and the defendant is still to comply with GPS monitoring and may return to his home but is not to come onto the school grounds at all.  Next date remains as set.
